hpnicfFcPing.name: hpnicfFcPing

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

hpnicfFcPing.description: This MIB module is for the management of the Fibre Channel Ping functionality.

hpnicfFcPingTable.name: hpnicfFcPingTable
hpnicfFcPingTable.description: A table of FC ping entries containing a group of FC ping requests that need to be executed at the agent.

hpnicfFcPingEntry.name: hpnicfFcPingEntry
hpnicfFcPingEntry.description: A FC ping request entry that need to be executed at the agent.

hpnicfFcPingIndex.name: hpnicfFcPingIndex
hpnicfFcPingIndex.description: The index of the current FC ping entry. This object identifies a FC ping request entry uniquely in a specified VSAN (Virtual Storage Area Network).

hpnicfFcPingVsan.name: hpnicfFcPingVsan
hpnicfFcPingVsan.description: The VSAN on which the FC ping request will be performed. If the corresponding instance value of hpnicfFcPingOperStatus is 'inProgress', the object cannot be modified.

hpnicfFcPingAddressType.name: hpnicfFcPingAddressType
hpnicfFcPingAddressType.description: The type of the corresponding instance of hpnicfFcPingAddress object.

hpnicfFcPingAddress.name: hpnicfFcPingAddress
hpnicfFcPingAddress.description: The address to which the route will be pinged. This object will contain an 8 octet long WWN(World Wide Name), if the value of the associated instance of hpnicfFcPingAddressType object is 'wwn'. This object will contain a 3 octet long Fibre Channel Address ID, if the value of the associated instance of hpnicfFcPingAddressType object is 'fcid'.

hpnicfFcPingPacketCount.name: hpnicfFcPingPacketCount
hpnicfFcPingPacketCount.description: The number of FC ping packets to be sent to the target in this sequence.

hpnicfFcPingPayloadSize.name: hpnicfFcPingPayloadSize
hpnicfFcPingPayloadSize.description: This object specifies the size of the FC ping packet payload to be sent to the target in this sequence.

hpnicfFcPingTimeout.name: hpnicfFcPingTimeout
hpnicfFcPingTimeout.description: The value of timeout for this FC ping request.

hpnicfFcPingDelay.name: hpnicfFcPingDelay
hpnicfFcPingDelay.description: The minimum amount of time to wait before sending the next packet in a sequence, after receiving a response or declaring a timeout for a previously transmitted packet.

hpnicfFcPingAgeInterval.name: hpnicfFcPingAgeInterval
hpnicfFcPingAgeInterval.description: The interval time after a FC ping test completes before the entry is aged out.

hpnicfFcPingAdminStatus.name: hpnicfFcPingAdminStatus
hpnicfFcPingAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of each hpnicfFcPingEntry. The object has two values: enable - Activate the entry. disable - Deactivate the entry. When the FC ping entry is executing, this object cannot be modified. If this object is read at such a time, a value of 'enable' will be returned. When the test finishes, the value of this object will be set to 'disable'.

hpnicfFcPingOperStatus.name: hpnicfFcPingOperStatus
hpnicfFcPingOperStatus.description: This object indicates the operational status of this hpnicfFcPingEntry. The value specifications are listed as follows: inProgress - FC ping is in progress. complete - FC ping is complete. disabled - FC ping is disabled. failed - FC ping has failed due to resource limitations.

hpnicfFcPingTrapOnCompletion.name: hpnicfFcPingTrapOnCompletion
hpnicfFcPingTrapOnCompletion.description: This object indicates that if hpnicfFcPingCompletionNotify notification should be generated or not when the corresponding ping sequence completes.

hpnicfFcPingRowStatus.name: hpnicfFcPingRowStatus
hpnicfFcPingRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

hpnicfFcPingStatTable.name: hpnicfFcPingStatTable
hpnicfFcPingStatTable.description: A table of FC ping statistics. This table notes the FC ping statistics of a FC ping test associated with an entry in the hpnicfFcPingTable.

hpnicfFcPingStatEntry.name: hpnicfFcPingStatEntry
hpnicfFcPingStatEntry.description: A FC ping statistics entry. An entry will be created automatically in this table when the hpnicfFcPingRowStatus of a ping request in the hpnicfFcPingTable is set to 'active'. The entry in this table will have the same indices as the entry that in the hpnicfFcPingTable. An entry in this table will be deleted when the corresponding entry in the hpnicfFcPingTable is deleted.

hpnicfFcPingReqPackets.name: hpnicfFcPingReqPackets
hpnicfFcPingReqPackets.description: The number of FC ping packets request in this sequence.

hpnicfFcPingResPackets.name: hpnicfFcPingResPackets
hpnicfFcPingResPackets.description: The number of FC ping packets response in this sequence.

hpnicfFcPingMinTime.name: hpnicfFcPingMinTime
hpnicfFcPingMinTime.description: The minimum round trip time of all the packets that have been sent in this sequence.

hpnicfFcPingAverageTime.name: hpnicfFcPingAverageTime
hpnicfFcPingAverageTime.description: The average round trip time of all the packets that have been sent in this sequence.

hpnicfFcPingMaxTime.name: hpnicfFcPingMaxTime
hpnicfFcPingMaxTime.description: The maximum round trip time of all the packets that have been sent in this sequence.

hpnicfFcPingTimeoutNum.name: hpnicfFcPingTimeoutNum
hpnicfFcPingTimeoutNum.description: The number of timeouts encountered in this sequence.

hpnicfFcPingCompletionNotify.name: hpnicfFcPingCompletionNotify
hpnicfFcPingCompletionNotify.description: When a FC ping test is finished and the instance of hpnicfFcPingTrapOnCompletion associated with the test is set to 'true', this notification occurred.
